    <learningContentbody>
        <lcInstruction>
            <ol id="ol_f2v_hxt_sxb">
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">Let's use the competency questions from the previous lesson as a
                        terminology source for beginning to specify terms in our ontology.</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">Open the PDF documents under "Card-Sorting Activity."</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">Start with the first file ("Bibliographic Record Unlabeled").</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">You will see a series of numbered cards with information extracted
                        from a MARC 21 Bibliographic record for the novel <i>Cien a√±os de
                            soledad</i>.</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">The cards are in the order they appear in the record. When a card
                        has decimal numbers, it means that the data elements come from the same
                        field.</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">Using the numbers, group the cards into categories.</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">Try to identify the types of entities that are represented.</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">Once you identify a group, give it a name and write down the
                        criteria used for creating it.</p>
                </li>
                <li dir="ltr">
                    <p dir="ltr">For example, "New York" is a type of Place (or City, or Populated
                        Place, which are specific kinds of Place).</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </lcInstruction>
